All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
Appointment
The Appointment class represents an appointment in the system.
AppointmentController
Controller class for managing appointments in the application.
AppointmentDAO
Data Access Object (DAO) class for managing appointments in the database.
Contact
The Contact class represents a contact entity, which can be found in our database in the "contacts" table.
ContactDAO
Data Access Object (DAO) for managing contacts in the database.
Customer
Represents a customer entity, of which all fields can be found in the "customers" table in the database.
CustomerDAO
The CustomerDAO class is a Data Access Object (DAO) responsible for managing customer data in the database.
CustomerManagementController
Controller class for managing customers.
CustomerSummary
The CustomerSummary class represents a summary of customer information.
JDBC
JDBC class manages the database connection, authentication, and user-related functionalities.
LoginController
Controller class for the login functionality.
Main
The Main class for the application.
ReportRow
The ReportRow class represents the three reports for the ReportsView screen.
ReportsController
Controller class for generating reports.
UserDAO
The UserDAO class provides methods for accessing and authenticating user data in the database.
